










TAPE and DISK operations

Tape and disk operations use concept of device priority.
First drive has number 1 and has highest priority, second drive has number 2, etc. Tape has number 9. 

LOAD <filename> - load Basic program from default mass storage
LOAD <filename> CODE - load binary file from default mass storage to memory location stated in file header
LOAD <filename> DATA <variable name> - load variable file from default mass storage and store it to a variable
LOAD <drive>,<filename> - load Basic program from mass storage device <drive>

SAVE <filename> - save Basic program to default mass storage
SAVE <filename> CODE <address>,<length> - save binary file to default mass storage from memory address, length gives number of bytes
SAVE <filename> DATA <variable> - save variable to default mass storage
SAVE <drive>,<filename> - save Basic program to mass storage device <drive>

VERIFY <filename>
MERGE <filename>

